Volunteers have been aiding local authorities in the search.

Police say Montgomery was home for Thanksgiving when he met up  with some friends  at the crowded Kildare's bar.

Authorities say he became separated from them and was escorted out by a bouncer around 2am Thursday after stumbling on a bar stool. 

In the wake of his disappearance, Jim Townsend, the director of operations at Kildare's, came forward to shed light on what happened when Montgomery was last seen.

A search of the records at the bar turned up a tab for Montgomery totaling $17, which Townsend said was for three craft beers.

He said that Montgomery did not appear intoxicated and though he bumped into the DJ table accidentally, he was polite about it.

